<h5 id="subject_55980">
<a href="?PHPSESSID=d6c7ff8d7e6e6b36d5cd3fe3c34b7c33&amp;topic=7603.msg55980#msg55980" rel="nofollow">转：[◇ Vampire：The AD&amp;D style]</a>
</h5>
<div class="zh_convert" style="float:right;display:none">
[<a href="javascript:convertToTraditional(document.getElementById('msg_55980'));undefined;">繁</a>
<a href="javascript:convertToSimplified (document.getElementById('msg_55980'));undefined;">简</a>]</div>
<div class="smalltext">&#171; <strong> 于:</strong> 2006-03-21, 周二 12:03:50 &#187;</div>
<div id="msg_55980_quick_mod"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_55980"><a href="http://bbs.ee.ntu.edu.tw/boards/TRPG/14/1/2/5/4.html" class="bbc_link new_win" target="_blank">原链接</a><br>（我也只是把繁体弄成了简体而已）<br><br>◇ Vampire：The AD&amp;D style<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>作者: Gerbil (猴岛小沙鼠) 看板: TRPG<br>标题: Vampire：The AD&amp;D style<br>时间: Mon Sep &nbsp;7 00:35:01 1998<br><br><br>&nbsp;在某处找到的文章，虽然声明是写给两个系统都了解的人，不过我想对于AD&amp;D的老手，这篇可以应该会让你们比较容易了解Storytelling system。<br><br>&nbsp;因为我忘记是从哪找?淼奈恼拢所以原作者不详...等我找到再补上。:)<br>&nbsp;中文注解是我写的，同样的，请不要把他当一回事。:P<br><br>&nbsp;----------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Vampire: AD&amp;D Style<br><br>An important note for all concered. The information presented<br>here is writen from the point of view that the reader is familiar<br>with both the Storyteller Game System from White Wolf Games and<br>the AD&amp;D Game System from TSR/WoTC. It is also done without<br>consent of either publisher and is not done for profit on my part.<br>No attempt is made or implied to infringe on any copyright laws.<br>Thank you.<br><br>Stat Conversions:<br>Vampire to AD&amp;D<br>属性对照<br>Strength = Strength<br>Dexterity = Dexterity<br>Stamina = Constitution<br>Charisma+Manipulation/2 = Charisma<br>Appearance = Comeliness<br>Perception = Perception (from Dragon Magazine)<br>Intelligence = Intelligence<br>Wits = Wisdom<br><br>(这边的dot就是storytelling system的代表数值的小圆点，最多到10点)<br>1 dot = score of 8<br>2 dots = score of 10<br>3 dots = score of 13<br>4 dots = score of 16<br>5 dots = score of 18<br><br>6 dots = score of 20<br>7 dots = score of 22<br>8 dots = score of 23<br>9 dots = score of 24<br>10 dots = score of 25<br><br>(角色的技能在storytelling system中是必要的设定，而且比较繁杂)<br>Talents, Skills and Knowledges are proficiancies in AD&amp;D,<br>which would not be optional in this case.<br><br>(下面的各项属性并非各个storytelling system都通用，而是依照各个不同<br>&nbsp;的Compaign setting而异)<br>Advantages: Disciplines, Backgrounds, and Virtues. These are<br>new stats that must be generated for the fledgling Kindred.<br>(info on MAGE: The Ascension and the other Storyteller Games<br>&nbsp;will follow later.....)<br><br>(美德与人性的设定与阵营相关，这边原作者并没有写得很清楚)<br>Virtues and Humanity, are linked to Alignment....( the Roads<br>&nbsp;and Virtues found in Dark Ages and the Sabbot are not going<br>&nbsp;to be detailed here.....Please Email me on that thank-you)<br><br>(对照表)<br>The Rankings of Virtues to Alignment<br>CONSCIENCE (Good vs. Evil)<br>1-Chaste: Evil Only<br>2-Moral: Max Evil and Min Neutral<br>3-Just: Min Good and Max Neutral<br>4-Charitable: Good Only<br>5-Remorseful: Good Only<br><br>Self-Control (Law vs Chaos)<br>1-Calm: Chaotic Only<br>2-Temperate: Max Chaotic and Min Neutral<br>3-Disciplined: Min Lawful and Max Neutral<br>4-Hardened: Lawful Only<br>5-Total Self-Mastery: Lawful Only<br><br>(勇气对照AD&amp;D的Level我是觉得怪怪的...有人能解释这个吗?)<br>COURAGE (based on Level of the PC)<br>1-Bold<br>2-Dauntless<br>3-Steadfast: Must be Name Level<br>4-Gallant: Must be Greater than 15th Level<br>5-Valorous: Must be 20th+ Level<br><br>(人性=阵营)<br>Humanity and Alignment:<br>0-Monstrous = Chaotic Evil<br>1-Horrific = Chaotic Evil<br>2-Beastial = Chaotic Evil<br>3-Cold = Chaotic Evil<br>4-Unfeeling = Chaotic Evil, Neutral Evil or Neutral<br>5-Distant = Chaotic Evil, Chaotic Neutral, Neutral<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Evil or Neutral<br>6-Removed = Any Alignment is Possible<br>7-Normal = Neutral, Neutral Good, Lawful Neutral or<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Lawful Good<br>8-Caring = Neutral Good or Lawful Good<br>9-Compassionate = Lawful Good<br>10-Humane = Lawfufl Good<br><br>As with the Standard VAMPIRE game, Conscience + Self-Control =<br>&nbsp;Humanity. But these base stats are determind by the character&#39;s<br>&nbsp;alignment.<br><br>(背景也包含在AD&amp;D设定的&quot;技能&quot;中，也是怪怪的，AD&amp;D角色的身份地位或关系应该是不用花点数?砩璧牟哦浴)<br>Backgrounds: These can be worked out as &quot;proficiencies&quot; as can<br>many other stats as well. I will not detail any info here as it<br>is up to the DM to decide point cost for his own game.<br><br>(这个WILLPOWER比较象是starwar里面CP的设计，AD&amp;D没有吧。我想。)<br>The Storyteller Trait of WILLPOWER, deserves special attention in<br>AD&amp;D. The trait in Storyteller is rolled against and can be spent<br>for special actions. Translating this into AD&amp;D truely is not<br>difficult.<br><br>1) Willpower = Hero Points (for those familier with Living City<br>campaigns this will not be new to you....for those without that<br>information. Hero Points=Hit Dice at a max.....and yes, non-<br>Kindred can use it too.) Just use it like spending Willpower in<br>Storyteller :-)<br><br>2) This is the part of Willpower that goes with &quot;saving&quot; vs<br>Domination and the like. Again it is based on the number of<br>Hit Dice the character has using the following converstions:<br>WILLPOWER and ADJUSTEMENT to specific Saves in AD&amp;D<br>1-Weak = -4<br>2-Timid = -3<br>3-Unassertive = -2<br>4-Diffident = -1<br>5-Certain = 0 no bonus no penalty<br>6-Confident = +1<br>7-Strong = +2<br>8-Controled = +3<br>9-Iron-Willed = +4<br>10-Unshakable = +5<br><br>Keep in mind the the Willpower Rating is based on Hit Dice.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div>
